  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my HESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit HESCO reference number in the bill checker above and click Check Bill. Your complete HESCO electricity bill appears in seconds — covering Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Nawabshah, Badin, or Thatta. Free, no login, 24/7." },
    { question: "What is the difference between HESCO and SEPCO?", answer: "HESCO covers lower and central Sindh: Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Tharparkar, Badin, Thatta, Nawabshah, and Sanghar. SEPCO covers upper Sindh: Sukkur, Larkana, Khairpur, Ghotki, Jacobabad, and Shikarpur. Check your bill heading to confirm which company you belong to." },
    { question: "How do I check my HESCO bill for Tharparkar?", answer: "Tharparkar is under HESCO's service area. Enter your 14-digit reference number in the checker above — it works for Mithi, Chachro, Islamkot, and Nagarparkar. In remote desert areas, paper bill delivery is unreliable — always check online to know your due date and avoid late payment surcharges." },
    { question: "How do I download my HESCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After the bill loads, click Download PDF and select Save as PDF in the browser print dialog. Your HESCO duplicate bill downloads instantly as a PDF — ready for payment at Easypaisa, JazzCash, or any bank in Hyderabad or interior Sindh." },
    { question: "How do I pay my HESCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, or any bank app. Select Electricity, choose HESCO or WAPDA, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify amount, and confirm. Easypaisa has excellent agent coverage in interior Sindh for cash payments." },
    { question: "What is the HESCO grace period?", answer: "HESCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After 7 days, a 10% surcharge applies. In areas where bills arrive late by post, always check your due date online before paying." },
    { question: "How do I check the HESCO load shedding schedule?", answer: "Visit ccms.pitc.com.pk and enter your 14-digit HESCO reference number. Your specific feeder's schedule appears. Hyderabad city typically sees 6–10 hours of load shedding; rural interior Sindh areas can see 12–18 hours depending on feeder recovery rates." },
    { question: "How do I apply for a new HESCO connection?", answer: "Apply at enc.com.pk and select HESCO as your distribution company. Or visit your nearest HESCO division office in Hyderabad, Mirpurkhas, Nawabshah, or your district. Upload CNIC and property documents for online applications." },
    { question: "How do I file a billing complaint with HESCO?", answer: "Call 022-9200301 or 118 with your reference number. Get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN). HESCO must resolve within 14 working days. Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 if ignored." },
